David Dunn is under consideration to replace James Beattie as manager of Accrington Stanley.

The 34-year-old Blackburn midfielder is open to the idea of a player-manager role at the League Two club. 

Beattie, 36, left Accrington by mutual consent on Friday after 16 months in charge.

